cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper focuses on using deep learning techniques to design a scheduler for deep learning clusters. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with efficient resource scheduling in deep learning clusters, which is a key aspect of distributed and cluster computing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of AI-driven services in deep learning clusters and proposes a DL-driven scheduler. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with designing a system (i.e., a scheduler) for controlling the allocation of resources in deep learning clusters. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses neural networks for both offline supervised learning and online reinforcement learning to optimize the resource allocation in deep learning clusters.
